<h3 id="org564513e">Describe why your organization will be a good Shapley Lecture host site:</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org564513e">
<p>
Pittsburgh is a hub for astronomy. The University of Pittsburgh (PITT)
hosts the Pittsburgh Particle Physics Astrophysics and Cosmology
Center (PITTPACC) and Carnegie Mellon University (CMU) hosts the
McWilliams Center for Cosmology &amp; Astrophysics. The Amateur
Astronomers Association of Pittsburgh (AAAP) has 500 active members.
We have a vibrant public education community, which includes seven
institutes for higher education and lifelong learning centers (OSHER)
at PITT and CMU. We have strong connections with local public
libraries, the Pittsburgh public schools, the Kamin Science Center and
Allegheny Observatory.
</p>
</div>
</div>


